"{\n  \"text\": \"There is a life web within the soil. This is, it starts with bacteria and acacia and funguses and all these very small organisms that are living within the soil that are processing all the different calories and all the different minerals and vitamins within the soil to provide to the plants. It starts with the single-celled organisms and it moves all the way up from the, you know, those to the nematodes and the multi-cell organisms that eat those until we get to earthworms and flies and crickets and all the things that are eating the multi-cell organisms that are eating all those things. This is the life web. This is what we need because it gives our food a complete bacterial profile. And that's so important for our digestion because without that, we'll be missing the nutrients that when they're available, sometimes they're available, sometimes they're not. But we won't be digesting because they won't have the complement of the bacteria that we need. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" There is a life web within the soil.\",\n      \"start\": 0.16,\n      \"end\": 3.04,\n      \"duration\": 2.88,\n      \"confidence\": 0.999,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Th\",\n          \"start\": 0.16,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ere\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" is\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" a\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" li\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 1.04,\n          \"dura